		<title>06FARMING cont.</title>
		<content> Chemicals make crops less resistant to
 disease and these then require further
 treatment with other chemicals which  
 can also be harmful to wildlife.      
                                       
 OTHER PRESENT DAY PROBLEMS:           
                                       
 Financial, especially since entry to  
 the E.E.C.                            
 Land values.                          
 Increased labour and equipment costs. 
 Higher standard of crops and meat     
 required.                             
 The increasingly technical side of    
 farming - knowing which chemicals to  
 use, etc.                             
 Old buildings unsuitable for modern   
 equipment.                            
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       </content>
